snippet.textDisplay:
I had the same A4 but in avant form with the same engine. Sold it at 360,000 miles on the clock and the engine was a delight. Couple of things I should mention:
1. The thermostat may not be the problem. These cars are famous for running cold (~60-70c).
2. Airbag warning went off all the time on mine as well - it's either a driver seat sensor or the comfort module that have gone.


Great choice though! I'm looking forward to seeing some kind of challenge with this car. Preferably a restoration job/economy challenge.
